{
  "texts": [
    "Pioneering this field of research, King et al.",
    "[51,52] showed that GANs are capable of generating syntheses of 2D flow fields after having been previously trained on direct numerical simulation (DNS) data.",
    "The reproductions even satisfied statistical constraints of turbulent flows, such as the Kolmogorov -5/3 law and the small-scale intermittency of turbulence.",
    "Using an unsupervised trained combination of a GAN and a recurrent neural network (RNN), Kim and Lee synthesized boundary conditions for turbulent flow [53] or generated stationary DNS flow fields [54].With the use of more advanced GAN frameworks such as conditional GAN (cGAN), turbulence can be predicted and controlled [55], even only at specific local points [56].",
    "[57] investigated the task of inferring a velocity component from the measurement of a second one for a rotating turbulent flow."
  ]
}